text: Aleksandra Polańska (born 24 September 2000) is a Polish swimmer. She competed in the women's 200 metre freestyle at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships and she did not advance to compete in the semi-finals. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Polish female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Polish female freestyle swimmers
